  "note": [
    {
      "text": "Grade 1 per CTCAE v5.0. Bilateral fingertip numbness and tingling, no motor component. Attributed to cumulative carboplatin toxicity. Gabapentin 300 mg PO at bedtime initiated for symptomatic management."
    },
    {
      "text": "2025-03-10 (Cycle 4): Improved from grade 2 at Cycle 3 to grade 1 on gabapentin 300 mg QHS. Numbness now limited to fingertip tips bilaterally, not interfering with daily activities. Carboplatin dose reduction from Cycle 3 maintained."
    }
